---
description: Project-wide engineering standards
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow these rules for all work in this repository.

- Use `pnpm` only. Prefer workspace commands like `pnpm --filter <package> ...`. Do not use `npm`, `yarn`, or `bun` unless explicitly requested.
- Apply SOLID principles where they improve maintainability. Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Keep routes, controllers, and UI handlers thin. Put business logic in services or domain modules.
- Write concise, readable, maintainable TypeScript. Prefer explicit names, focused functions, and simple control flow.
- Follow existing project conventions and structure. Keep diffs small and avoid unrelated refactors.
- Prefer strict typing. Avoid `any` unless clearly justified.
- Add or update tests for every non-trivial change, bug fix, or new behavior.
- Run relevant tests before considering work complete. If shared behavior changed, run the broader related suite as well.
- Validate inputs, handle errors explicitly, and do not expose secrets or tokens.
- Reuse shared workspace packages before duplicating logic.
